
=======================
HOW TO USE THE DEBUGGER
=======================

1. Source the environment variables to get access to all our licenses
                                source env.sh

2. 	Launch the simulation, udagent and openOCD by executing run_debugger script:

								$REPOROOT/dv/common/scripts/debugger/run_debugger

    2.1 If there is no simulation, the script will run a very simple python test using
        the IOShire standalone to create the build and simulation environment needed.

    2.2 Then, the rerun script will be changed to make it reusable in different runs and
        to disable the python script executed in section 2.1 in order to allow the debugger
        use the same socket.

    2.3 The run_debugger script looks for a free port and sets the environment variables properly
        before launching the simulation and the UDAgent and OpenOCD.

	2.4 Two log files will be created in the test run directory: openocd_log.log and 
        udagent_log.log

	2.5 UDAgent performs a discovery process to reach all the IOShire UltraSoc modules,
		you will see in the udagent log two tables that contain the modules to be discovered
		and the modules that have been discovered and the transactions between the udagent and 
        the simulator.

	2.6 Once openOCD is launched, the script will finish and run the UDAgent and openOCD as a 
		background process. 

	2.7 The openOCD log contain the information of the transactions between the udagent
		and the simulation.

3. 	On a different terminal you will have to wait until openOCD allows the GDB to connect, 
    in order to know when the GDB can connect you will have to grep the openOCD log file using 
    the next command:

						tail -f openocd_log.log  | grep Listening

	Wait until you are able to see the next line:
	"Info : 263 205394 server.c:311 add_service(): Listening on port 3333 for gdb connections"


4. 	Once openOCD allows the GDB to connect, open a new shell (or reuse the one in section 3) 
    and open the GDB by running the next command:

								./debugger/launch_gdb

	4.1 Connect to the openOCD through remote target by running the next command:
							target remote <machine>:3333

					<machine> = {localhost, sc-server07, sc-server05,...}

	4.2 It will take around 10-20 minutes to connect GDB with the openOCD. 

	4.3 In addition, you can see if the port for GDB has been opened by running netstat and
		looking for machine port 3333 service by running the next command:

								    netstat -lt4


5. 	Once you're connected and you have the GBD prompt available you will be able to start using
	the debugger. Take into account, that each command will take several minutes/hours since VCS is very
	slow.



